ficial%20intelligence%26quot%3B%20isn't%20%26quot%3Bthe%20future%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20a%20marketing%20term%20for%20a%20slightly%20updated%20version%20of%20the%20automation%20that%20has%20been%20ruling%20our%20lives%20for%20years.%20Companies%20have%20cycled%20through%20a%20series%20of%20names%20to%20dress%20up%20their%20tech%20%E2%80%94%20automation%2C%20algorithms%2C%20machine%20learning%2C%20and%20now%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20but%20ultimately%2C%20these%20systems%20all%20boil%20down%20to%20the%20same%20idea%3A%20handing%20over%20decision-making%20to%20computers%20to%20execute%20tasks%20at%20speeds%20far%20faster%20than%20a%20human%20could.%20While%20there's%20growing%20fear%20that%20a%20new%20breed%20of%20AI%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-lonelier-at-work-friends-connect-with-coworkers-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einfect%20our%20daily%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-radically-reshape-job-market-global-economy-employee-labor-innovation-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eput%20millions%20of%20people%20out%20of%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-is-guiding-humans-to-a-new-age-of-discovery-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerally%20upend%20society%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20most%20people%20don't%20realize%20just%20how%20deeply%20computerized%20decision-making%20has%20wormed%20its%20way%20into%20every%20facet%20of%20our%20existence.%20These%20systems%20are%20based%20on%20datasets%20and%20the%20rules%20that%20human%20beings%20teach%20them%2C%20but%20whether%20it's%20making%20money%20in%20the%20markets%20or%20feeding%20us%20the%20news%2C%20more%20and%20more%20of%20our%20lives%20are%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20unaccountable%20digital%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20cases%2C%20these%20algorithms%20have%20proven%20useful%20for%20society.%20They've%20helped%20eliminate%20mundane%20tasks%20or%20level%20the%20playing%20field.%20But%20increasingly%2C%20the%20algorithms%20that%20undergird%20our%20digital%20lives%20are%20making%20questionable%20decisions%20that%20enrich%20the%20powerful%20and%20wreck%20the%20lives%20of%20average%20people.%20There's%20no%20reason%20to%20be%20scared%20of%20AI%20making%20decisions%20for%20you%20in%20the%20future%20%E2%80%94%20computers%20have%20already%20been%20doing%20so%20for%20quite%20some%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20internet%20was%20a%20relatively%20human-curated%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20a%20disparate%20collection%20of%20web%20pages%20that%20were%20discoverable%20only%20if%20you%20knew%20the%20address%20of%20the%20site%20or%20saw%20a%20link%20to%20it%20on%20another%20site.%20That%20changed%20in%20June%201993%2C%20when%20the%20researcher%20Matthew%20Gray%20created%20one%20of%20the%20first%20%26quot%3Bweb%20robots%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20primitive%20algorithm%20designed%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclutejournals.com%2Findex.php%2FIJMIS%2Farticle%2Fdownload%2F5799%2F5877%2F23158%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeasure%20the%20size%20of%20the%20web%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Gray's%20invention%20helped%20create%20search%20engines%20and%20inspired%20a%20league%20of%20successors%20%E2%80%94%20Jump%20Station%2C%20Excite%2C%20Yahoo%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20In%201998%2C%20Stanford%20students%20Sergey%20Brin%20and%20Larry%20Page%20made%20the%20next%20leap%20in%20automating%20the%20internet%20when%20they%20published%20an%20academic%20paper%20about%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Finfolab.stanford.edu%2Fpub%2Fpapers%2Fgoogle.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge-scale%20hypertext%20web%20search%20engine%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20called%20Google.%20The%20paper%20detailed%20how%20their%20algorithm%C2%A0%26quot%3BPageRank%26quot%3B%20judged%20the%20importance%20of%20a%20web%20result%20based%20on%20a%20user's%20query%2C%20serving%20up%20the%20most%20relevant%20site%20based%20on%20how%20many%20other%20websites%20linked%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20which%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%20on%20a%20much%20smaller%20and%20more%20innocent%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20three%20decades%20after%20the%20founding%20of%20Google%2C%20the%20internet%20has%20only%20gotten%20more%20automated.%20This%20has%20come%20with%20plenty%20of%20benefits%20for%20average%20people%20%E2%80%94%20recommendations%20on%20Spotify%20and%20Netflix%20help%20us%20find%20new%20art%2C%20robo-investors%20can%20help%20grow%20a%20nest%20egg%20at%20a%20low%20cost%2C%20and%20industrial%20applications%20like%20the%20robotics%20used%20to%20manufacture%20many%20modern%20vehicles%20have%20made%20our%20economy%20more%20efficient.%20Somewhere%20along%20the%20way%2C%20however%2C%20the%20tech%20industry%20tipped%20over%20from%20helpfully%20automating%20the%20jobs%20that%20slowed%20down%20our%20lives%20to%20distorting%20society%20by%20surrendering%20crucial%20decisions%20to%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20original%20Google%20paper%20feels%20like%20a%20dark%20warning.%20It%20argues%20that%20advertising-funded%20search%20engines%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Binherently%20biased%26quot%3B%20toward%20those%20advertisers.%20It's%20probably%20no%20surprise%20then%20that%20researchers%20have%20found%20that%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsearchengineland.com%2Fex-google-search-head-worried-his-team-was-too-involved-with-ads-434050%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprioritizing%20ad%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20useful%20results%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-getting-worse-spam-affiliate-links-duckduckgo-bing-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20algorithm%20is%20getting%20worse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20degrading%20a%20crucial%20source%20of%20information%20for%20over%205%20billion%20people.%20And%20it's%20not%20just%20search%20engines.%20Revenue-focused%20algorithms%20behind%20networks%20like%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20TikTok%2C%20and%20Twitter%20have%20learned%20how%20to%20feed%20users%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20upsetting%20or%20enraging%20content%20to%20goose%20user%20engagement.%20As%20human%20control%20diminished%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstate-attorneys-general-investigate-tiktok-childrens-mental-health-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal-world%20consequences%20of%20these%20algorithms%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20piled%20up%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-internal-report-shows-instagram-bad-for-teens-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram's%20algorithm%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20a%20mental-health%20crisis%20in%20teenage%20girls.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-says-algorithm-biased-toward-right-wing-politicians-conservatives-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%20admitted%20that%20its%20tech%20%3C%2Fa%3Etended%20to%20amplify%20tweets%20from%20right-wing%20politicians%2C%20influencers%2C%20and%20news%20sources%2C%20and%20it's%20only%20grown%20worse%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-x-content-moderation-polices-california-law-ab587-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%20bought%20the%20site%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Cambridge%20Analytica%20used%20an%20algorithm%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcambridge-analytica-whistleblower-christopher-wylie-facebook-data-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrawl%20Facebook's%20data%20to%20hyper-target%20millions%20of%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20UK's%20vote%20to%20leave%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20the%202016%20US%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlgorithms%20that%20were%20supposed%20to%20make%20work%20easier%20or%20employees%20more%20productive%20have%20helped%20tilt%20the%20economy%20against%20blue-collar%20workers%20and%20people%20of%20color.%20Companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2021-06-28%2Ffired-by-bot-amazon-turns-to-machine-managers-and-workers-are-losing-out%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20Amazon%20%3C%2Fa%3Eare%20making%20hiring%20and%20firing%20decisions%20based%20on%20the%20whims%20of%20a%20glorified%20calculator.%20Customers%20are%20getting%20the%20short%20end%20of%20the%20AI%20stick%2C%20too%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthemarkup.org%2Fdenied%2F2021%2F08%2F25%2Fthe-secret-bias-hidden-in-mortgage-approval-algorithms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%202019%20investigation%20by%20the%20Associated%20Press%20and%20The%20Markup%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20algorithms%20used%20in%20making%20loan%20decisions%20were%20highly%20biased%20against%20people%20of%20color%2C%20with%20lenders%20being%2080%25%20more%20likely%20to%20turn%20down%20Black%20applicants%20than%20similar%20white%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20these%20problems%20carry%20over%20into%20the%20public%20sector%2C%20poisoning%20government%20services%20with%20algorithmic%20biases.%20The%20UK%20government%20faced%20a%20national%20scandal%20in%202020%20when%20administrators%20replaced%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20students'%20A-level%20exams%20%E2%80%94%20a%20crucial%20test%20that%20can%20determine%20a%20student's%20ability%20to%20go%20to%20university%20%E2%80%94%20with%20algorithmically%20chosen%20grades.%20The%20results%20significantly%20underscored%20students%20from%20Britain's%20tuition-free%20state%20schools%2C%20instead%20favoring%20those%20who%20went%20to%20private%20schools%20in%20affluent%20areas%20and%20throwing%20the%20lives%20of%20many%20young%20people%20into%20disarray.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fdutch-scandal-serves-as-a-warning-for-europe-over-risks-of-using-algorithms%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bself-learning%26quot%3B%20algorithm%20used%20by%20the%20Dutch%20tax%20authority%3C%2Fa%3E%20falsely%20penalized%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20for%20supposedly%20defrauding%20the%20country's%20childcare%20system%2C%20pushing%20people%20into%20poverty%20and%20leading%20to%20thousands%20of%20children%20being%20placed%20into%20foster%20care.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpropublica.org%2Farticle%2Fmachine-bias-risk-assessments-in-criminal-sentencing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProPublica%20found%20in%20a%202016%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20an%20algorithm%20used%20in%20multiple%20state%20court%20systems%20to%20judge%20how%20likely%20somebody%20was%20to%20commit%20a%20crime%20in%20the%20future%20was%20biased%20against%20Black%20Americans%2C%20leading%20to%20harsher%20sentences%20from%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20public%20and%20private%20sectors%2C%20we've%20handed%20the%20keys%20to%20a%20spiderweb%20of%20algorithms%20built%20with%20little%20public%20insight%20into%20how%20they%20make%20their%20decisions.%20There%20is%20some%20pushback%20to%20this%20infiltration%20%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.techtarget.com%2Fsearchenterpriseai%2Ffeature%2FFTC-pursues-AI-regulation-bans-biased-algorithms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20FTC%20is%20seeking%20to%20regulate%20how%20businesses%20use%20algorithms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20they've%20yet%20to%20do%20so%20meaningfully.%20And%20more%20broadly%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20governments%20are%20resigned%20to%20allowing%20machines%20to%20rule%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20the%20proverbial%20frog%20boiling%20in%20a%20pot%20of%20water%2C%20the%20slow%20takeover%20of%20algorithms%20has%20mostly%20gone%20unnoticed%20by%20the%20general%20public.%20It's%20easy%20to%20miss%20a%20small%20tweak%20to%20Instagram's%20algorithm%20or%20even%20celebrate%20the%20tax%20software%20that%20simplifies%20your%20filing.%20But%20now%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20new%20wave%20of%20%26quot%3Bartificial%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B