%20is%20deficient%2C%20and%20then%20once%20the%20PIP%20is%20over%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20sometimes%20even%20sooner%20%E2%80%94%20they%20terminate%20the%20employee%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20we%20outlined%20in%20the%20PIP%2C%20things%20weren't%20going%20well%20in%20certain%20areas.%20We%20don't%20feel%20like%20you've%20improved%2C%20so%20we're%20going%20to%20part%20ways%20with%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPIPs%20are%20a%20tool%20for%20companies%20to%20prevent%20litigation%2C%20too%2C%20because%20then%20they%20can%20argue%20that%20they%20didn't%20terminate%20the%20employee%20because%20of%20discrimination%2C%20retaliation%2C%20or%20sexual%20harassment%20but%20rather%20because%20of%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-if-placed-on-pip-microsoft-vp-leave-asap-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployee%20receives%20a%20PIP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20three%20steps%20that%20I%20suggest%20that%20they%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Read%20the%20PIP%20very%20carefully%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20are%20so%20shocked%20that%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-performance-improvement-plan-employee-tech-amazon-google-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceive%20a%20PIP%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20don't%20actually%20take%20the%20time%20to%20take%20a%20deep%20breath%2C%20sit%20down%2C%20and%20read%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20want%20to%20fully%20understand%20the%20language%20that's%20in%20the%20PIP%20and%20what%20the%20expectations%20are.%20If%20you%20need%20clarification%20because%20there's%20not%20enough%20information%2C%20you%20should%20go%20back%20and%20ask%20your%20company%20your%20questions%20and%20see%20if%20they%20offer%20support%2C%20such%20as%20one-on-one%20meetings%20with%20your%20supervisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Decide%20if%20the%20PIP%20is%20reasonable%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you've%20read%20the%20PIP%2C%20ask%20yourself%2C%20is%20this%20PIP%20designed%20for%20me%20to%20fail%2C%20or%20is%20it%20reasonable%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-performance-improvement-plan-how-to-survive-career-development-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20PIP%20should%20be%20very%20clear%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20areas%20where%20the%20employee%20is%20supposedly%20deficient.%20In%20a%20reasonable%20timeframe%2C%20it%20should%20spell%20out%20how%20that%20employee%20will%20get%20better%20and%20offer%20support%20such%20as%20regular%20meetings%20with%20their%20supervisor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bad%20PIP%20is%20very%20short%20and%20doesn't%20articulate%20the%20areas%20in%20which%20the%20employee%20needs%20to%20get%20better%2C%20so%20the%20employee%20is%20left%20confused%20and%20doesn't%20know%20what%20is%20being%20asked%20of%20them.%20There%20either%20isn't%20a%20timeframe%20given%2C%20or%20the%20timeframe%20is%20unreasonable%2C%20and%20no%20support%20is%20offered%20to%20help%20the%20employee%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20receiving%20a%20bad%20PIP%2C%20the%20employee%20walks%20away%20confused%20or%20feeling%20unreasonable.%20Typically%2C%20when%20an%20employee%20receives%20a%20bad%20PIP%2C%20it%20means%20the%20company%20doesn't%20want%20them%20to%20improve.%20It's%20just%20a%20tool%20to%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20the%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Decide%20whether%20to%20respond%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20after%20reading%20your%20PIP%2C%20you%20feel%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperformance-improvement-plan-pip-survived-teacher-better-employee-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eactually%20pretty%20reasonable%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20you%20can%20satisfy%20the%20requirements%20in%20the%20time%20allotted%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20respond.%20Just%20move%20on%20and%20focus%20on%20working%20on%20what's%20needed%20and%20satisfying%20the%20requirements%20laid%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20sometimes%2C%20there%20are%20unfair%20PIPs%20with%20requirements%20that%20even%20the%20best%20employee%20in%20the%20world%20could%20never%20satisfy.%20If%20the%20PIP%20is%20unrealistic%20or%20unreasonable%2C%20then%20you%20need%20to%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20decide%20to%20respond%2C%20email%20your%20supervisor%20or%20HR%20and%20spell%20out%20why%20it%20is%20unreasonable.%20Perhaps%20the%20timeframe%20is%20not%20long%20enough%2C%20or%20the%20expectations%20are%20unattainable%2C%20or%20the%20company%20isn't%20offering%20any%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20spelling%20out%20the%20ways%20the%20PIP%20is%20unreasonable%2C%20it%20can%20protect%20your%20interests%20a%20bit%20in%20the%20event%20that%20you%20are%20later%20terminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EIs%20the%20PIP%20retaliatory%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20also%20think%20about%20whether%20the%20PIP%20is%20retaliatory.%20A%20lot%20of%20companies%20will%20issue%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommon-mistakes-employers-companies-result-settlements-workers-lawsuits-attorneys-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPIP%20in%20retaliation%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20employee%20complaining%20about%20something%20illegal%20going%20on%20in%20the%20workplace%20or%20taking%20leave%20for%20disabilities%20or%20pregnancy%2C%20which%20is%20protected%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fagencies%2Fodep%2Fpublications%2Ffact-sheets%2Femployment-laws-medical-and-disability-related-leave%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFamily%20and%20Medical%20Leave%20Act%20(FMLA)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeave%20is%20there%20for%20a%20reason.%20If%20you%20have%20a%20disability%2C%20if%20you%20have%20mental%20health%20issues%2C%20or%20if%20you're%20pregnant%2C%20then%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnearly-half-american-workers-dont-take-all-their-pto-research-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneed%20to%20use%20your%20leave%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20that's%20precisely%20what%20they're%20there%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20I%20see%20all%20the%20time%20that%20companies%20perceive%20employees%20who%20take%20leave%20to%20be%20a%20burden.%20Companies%20don't%20like%20when%20they%20have%20somebody%20out%20of%20work%20and%20they%20have%20to%20satisfy%20those%20duties%2C%20either%20by%20hiring%20somebody%20to%20fill%20in%20or%20asking%20somebody%20else%20to%20take%20on%20those%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20happens%20far%20too%20often%20across%20the%20US.%20When%20you%20look%20at%20other%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20how%20they%20value%20leave%20and%20how%20much%20time%20off%20they%20give%20people%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20more%20emphasis%20on%20quality%20of%20life%20rather%20than%20the%20American%20way%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-ireland-us-american-hustle-culture-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efocused%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bgrind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20American%20companies%20put%20so%20much%20more%20emphasis%20on%20the%20bottom%20line%20and%20making%20money%20and%20less%20on%20employee%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20believe%20your%20PIP%20is%20due%20to%20your%20company%20retaliating%20against%20you%2C%20then%20you%20can%20respond%20in%20writing%3B%20articulate%20what%20you%20believe%20the%20PIP%20is%20in%20retaliation%20for%2C%20and%20spell%20out%20the%20illegal%20conduct.%20Keep%20a%20copy%20of%20that%20email%20so%20that%20in%20the%20event%20that%20you%20do%20get%20terminated%20in%20the%20future%2C%20you're%20preserving%20the%20record%20for%20purposes%20of%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I'm%20speaking%20with%20clients%2C%20I%20look%20at%20the%20full%20picture%20because%2C%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20I%20see%20a%20situation%20where%20an%20employee%20was%20a%20strong%20performer%20for%20many%20years%20and%20received%20good%20performance%20evaluations%2C%20but%20then%20they%20complained%20about%20something%20illegal%20or%20took%20protected%20medical%20leave%20and%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20they%20received%20the%20PIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20me%2C%20that%20doesn't%20add%20up.%20You%20don't%20just%20suddenly%20become%20a%20bad%20performer%20when%20you%20have%20a%20documented%20history%20of%20strong%20performance%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20better%20for%20companies%20to%20work%20with%20employees%20rather%20than%20use%20PIPs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20philosophy%20is%20that%20it's%20better%20for%20supervisors%20to%20sit%20down%2C%20talk%20to%20the%20employee%2C%20and%20sort%20of%20nip%20issues%20in%20the%20bud%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20recognize%20potential%20areas%20of%20deficiencies%20and%20deal%20with%20them%20right%20away%20rather%20than%20letting%20things%20fester.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20companies%20have%20already%20decided%20to%20terminate%20the%20employee%20by%20the%20time%20they%20get%20to%20a%20PIP.%20If%20I%20were%20running%20a%20business%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20issue%20a%20PIP.%20I%20would%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feffective-feedback-should-be-a-two-way-conversation-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esit%20down%20with%20the%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20or%20twice%20and%20genuinely%20explain%20how%20I%20wanted%20them%20to%20get%20better.%20You%20can%20still%20have%20a%20paper%20trail%20by%20sending%20a%20follow-up%20email%20outlining%20what%20was%20discussed%20and%20areas%20for%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-quiet-quit-director-three-months-walking-out-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emindset%20around%20PIPs%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20change.%20Companies%20should%20want%20their%20employees%20to%20improve%2C%20and%20they%20should%20deal%20with%20problems%20early%20on%20rather%20than%20just%20issuing%20PIPs%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20employment%20and%20then%20terminating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%