dence%2C%20trade%20secrets%20or%20intellectual%20property%2C%20the%20disclosure%20of%20which%20would%20harm%20the%20competitive%20position%20of%20a%20third%20party%2C%20unless%20the%20competent%20authority%20is%20satisfied%20that%20larger%20public%20interest%20warrants%20the%20disclosure%20of%20such%20information%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20has%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20state-run%20bank%20has%20%26quot%3Bblandly%20invoked%20the%20exemption%20clause%20without%20demonstrating%20how%20the%20disclosure%20would%20'harm%20the%20competitive%20position%20of%20a%20third%20party'.%20The%20denial%20will%20be%20challenged%20in%20appeal%2C%20she%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20development%20comes%20weeks%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20pulled%20up%20SBI%20for%20the%20delay%20in%20sharing%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20with%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%20Following%20the%20landmark%20verdict%20in%20February%20that%20scrapped%20the%20poll%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20the%20bank%20had%20sought%20three%20months'%20time%20to%20share%20the%20data.%20The%20court%2C%20however%2C%20refused%20its%20request%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20make%20the%20data%20public%20within%20two%20days.%20The%20court%20also%20warned%20that%20it%20will%20initiate%20contempt%20proceedings%20against%20the%20bank%20if%20it%20did%20not%20disclose%20the%20data%20at%20the%20earliest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20bank%20shared%20the%20data%2C%20it%20came%20in%20for%20another%20round%20of%20reprimand%20from%20the%20court.%20The%20court%20asked%20why%20the%20bank%20had%20not%20disclosed%20the%20bond%20numbers.%20Thereafter%2C%20the%20bank%20shared%20the%20details%20and%20filed%20an%20affidavit%20declaring%20that%20it%20had%20disclosed%20all%20information%20related%20to%20the%20poll%20bonds%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20February%2015%20judgment%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20scrapped%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20violates%20the%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information.%20The%20scheme%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%2C%20was%20unconstitutional%20and%20arbitrary%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangement%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20bench%20of%20five%20judges%20held%20that%20the%20stated%20objective%20of%20fighting%20black%20money%20and%20maintaining%20the%20confidentiality%20of%20donors%20cannot%20defend%20the%20scheme.%20Electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20are%20not%20the%20only%20way%20to%20curb%20black%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712046720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Ft9f561vc_sbi_625x300_15_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fstate-bank-of-india-rti-electoral-bonds-scheme-in-rti-reply-sbi-refuses-to-share-info-on-its-electoral-bond-guidelines-5357901%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Weeks%20after%20it%20was%20pulled%20up%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20issue%2C%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20refused%20to%20reveal%20details%20of%20the%20Standard%20Operating%20Procedures%20issued%20to%20its%20branches%20regarding%20sale%20and%20redemption%20of%20electoral%20bonds%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fstate-bank-of-india-rti-electoral-bonds-scheme-in-rti-reply-sbi-refuses-to-share-info-on-its-electoral-bond-guidelines-5357901%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fstate-bank-of-india-rti-electoral-bonds-scheme-in-rti-reply-sbi-refuses-to-share-info-on-its-electoral-bond-guidelines-5357901%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fstate-bank-of-india-rti-electoral-bonds-scheme-in-rti-reply-sbi-refuses-to-share-info-on-its-electoral-bond-guideli