ements%20following%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Frussiaukraine-war%5C%22%3Einvasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20pushed%20the%20country%20from%20being%20the%20second-largest%20arms%20exporter%2C%20just%20behind%20the%20United%20States%2C%20to%20the%20third-largest%20today.%20The%20second%20place%20is%20now%20claimed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffrance-sends-rocket-launchers-more-arms-to-ukraine-emmanuel-macron-3624739%5C%22%3EFrance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20China%20retains%20the%20fourth%20position.%20India%2C%20both%20as%20an%20arms%20importer%2C%20and%20increasingly%2C%20an%20exporter%20too%2C%20will%20naturally%20have%20to%20adjust%20to%20these%20changed%20dynamics%2C%20primarily%20because%20Russia%20is%20a%20leading%20supplier%20of%20arms%20to%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussian%20Imports%20Waning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Russia%20is%20still%20the%20top%20supplier%20for%20India%2C%20the%20share%20of%20imports%20has%20decreased%20to%2036%25%2C%20compared%20to%20over%2076%25%20between%202009%20and%202013.%20France%20was%20a%20close%20second%2C%20making%20up%2033%25%20of%20the%20imports%20in%20the%202019-2023%20period%2C%20while%20the%20U.S.%20accounted%20for%2013%25%20of%20the%20imports.%20The%20slide%20in%20Russian%20imports%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20new%20and%20is%20a%20product%20of%20three%20well-known%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20increasing%20threats%20from%20China%20have%20necessitated%20the%20need%20for%20more%20sophisticated%20weapons%2C%20and%20this%20has%20elevated%20the%20position%20of%20suppliers%20like%20the%20U.S.%2C%20Israel%2C%20and%20France%2C%20which%20are%20more%20capable%20of%20supplying%20advanced%20systems.%20Second%2C%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%20in%202014%20had%20already%20created%20obstacles%20in%20procuring%20Russian%20equipment.%20The%20subsequent%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022%20exacerbated%20New%20Delhi's%20predicament%20as%20the%20U.S.%20sanctions%20regime%20threatened%20to%20hurt%20companies%20and%20countries%20that%20continued%20to%20import%20Russian%20products.%20Third%2C%20India's%20policy%20to%20domestically%20manufacture%20arms%20under%20the%20Make%20in%20India%20initiative%20promotes%20indigenous%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20India%20Needs%20More%20Sophisticated%20Equipment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20demand%20for%20more%20sophisticated%20technology%20than%20what%20Russia%20can%20offer%20arises%20from%20the%20need%20to%20offset%20China's%20numerical%20superiority%20in%20weapons%20systems%2C%20from%20aircraft%20and%20drones%20to%20submarines%20and%20aircraft%20carriers.%20This%20is%20in%20line%20with%20the%20rationale%20underlying%20the%20US's%20'Second%20Offset%20Strategy'%2C%20which%20focuses%20on%20the%20development%20of%20precision%20weapons%20to%20counter%20Soviet%20numerical%20superiority%20in%20the%20European%20theatre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20among%20others%2C%20India%20last%20year%20acquired%20the%20Scorpene%20submarine%20from%20France%20and%20transferred%20the%20technology%20for%20indigenous%20production.%20It%20also%20acquired%20precision%20capabilities%20and%20munitions%20such%20as%20the%20Apache%20helicopters%20(with%2012%20Longbow%20radars)%2C%20the%20Harpoon%20anti-ship%20missiles%20and%20the%20Excalibur%20guided%20artillery%20shells.%20The%20US%20approved%20the%20purchase%20of%20a%20contract%20of%20roughly%20%244%20billion%20for%20the%20MQ9%20Reaper%20and%20Hellfire%20missiles%20this%20year%2C%20a%20testament%20to%20India's%20continued%20reliance%20on%20US%20sophisticated%20technology%20and%20the%20deepening%20defence%20ties%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFallout%20Of%20The%20Russia-Ukraine%20War%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20effects%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20on%20Indian%20defence%20procurement%20cannot%20be%20understated.%20From%202014%20onwards%2C%20sanctions%20imposed%20by%20the%20US%20and%20many%20other%20NATO%20(North%20Atlantic%20Treaty%20Organization)%20states%20led%20to%20problems%20in%20financing%20Russian%20imports.%20Most%20important%20among%20them%20was%20the%20Countering%20America's%20Adversaries%20Through%20Sanctions%20Act%20(CAATSA)%20of%202017%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20penalise%20countries%20that%20acquired%20defence%20equipment%20from%20Russia.%20Although%20India%20has%20repeatedly%20managed%20to%20win%20waivers%20from%20these%20measures%2C%20they%20still%20add%20an%20extra%20set%20of%20diplomatic%20and%20security-related%20transaction%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20loss%20of%20equipment%20in%20Ukraine%20in%202022%20also%20stymied%20exports%20to%20India.%20Deliveries%20of%20pre-existing%20orders%20have%20hindered%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force.%20Less%20commonly%20understood%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20because%20of%20its%20critical%20role%20in%20the%20Soviet%20defence%20industrial%20complex%2C%20Ukraine%20was%20also%20a%20defence%20supplier%20to%20India-especially%20in%20naval%20technology%2C%20like%20propulsion%20systems%20for%20Indian%20frigates-for%20complementary%20goods%20offered%20by%20Russia.%20This%20relationship%20is%20now%20over%20because%20of%20the%20war%20and%20the%20subsequent%20destruction%20of%20Ukraine's%20naval%20construction%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20push%20toward%20indigenous%20manufacturing%20of%20weapons%20is%20not%20new.%20Since%20the%201950s%2C%20India%20has%20sought%20to%20develop%20a%20domestic%20defence%20manufacturing%20sector%20with%20a%20combination%20of%20licensed%20production%20of%20foreign%20arms%20and%20indigenous%20development%20of%20new%20arms%2C%20through%20a%20group%20of%20public%20sector%20units%20and%20the%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20(DRDO).%20However%2C%20achievements%20like%20the%20Integrated%20Guided%20Missile%20Programme%2C%20initiated%20in%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20are%20exceptions.%20This%20has%20been%20due%20to%20both%20funding%20hassles%20for%20research%20and%20development%20and%20difficulty%20fulfilling%20the%20requirements%20issued%20by%20the%20armed%20forces.%20There%20is%20also%20criticism%20from%20some%20sections%20that%20requirements%20by%20the%20Indian%20military%20are%20allegedly%20modified%20and%20made%20more%20stringent%20for%20domestic%20manufacturers%2C%20while%20foreign%20firms%20are%20allowed%20to%20circumvent%20these.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Strategic%20Reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20often%20used%20its%20imports%20to%20enhance%20its%20indigenisation%20efforts.%20Like%20Israel%2C%20this%20allows%20for%20affordable%20but%20higher%20quality%20products%20that%20are%20suited%20to%20Indian%20needs.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20uses%20indigenous%20components%20in%20combination%20with%20systems%20like%20radars%20from%20Israel%20and%20platforms%20like%20the%20Embraer%20145%20jet%20from%20Brazil%2C%20and%20the%20Airbus%20A-321%20from%20France.%20India's%20Light%20Combat%20Aircraft%2C%20Tejas%20Mark%201%2C%20also%20has%20a%20GE-404%20engine%20from%20the%20US%20and%20an%20ejection%20seat%20made%20by%20Martin-Baker%20of%20Britain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20India's%20strategic%20position%20and%20realities%20today%20necessitate%20having%20a%20strong%2C%20functional%20military%20that's%20capable%20of%20patrolling%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20and%20maintaining%20border%20deterrence.%20There%20is%20now%20a%20complex%20choice%20that%20India%20has%20avoided%20making%20for%20years%3A%20rely%20either%20on%20Western%20states%20led%20by%20the%20US%20or%20on%20an%20increasingly%20inconsistent%20Russia.%20While%20the%20first%20option%20draws%20India%20further%20into%20an%20alignment%20with%20the%20existing%20global%20order%2C%20the%20latter%20requires%20dealing%20with%20a%20country%20that's%20beset%20with%20increased%20domestic%20demand%2C%20a%20sanctioned%20industrial%20base%2C%20and%20failing%20exports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20third%20option%20too%2C%20though%20this%20will%20require%20both%20time%20and%20policy%20commitment-developing%20a%20defence%20industrial%20base%20capable%20of%20equipping%20the%20world's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-was-worlds-4th-largest-defence-spender-in-2022-says-report-3981539%5C%22%3Ethird-largest%20military%20in%20terms%20of%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Benjamin%20Tkach%20is%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20Mississippi%20State%20University%2C%20and%20Vasabjit%20Banerjee%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Political%20Science%2C%20University%20of%20Tennessee%2C%20Knoxville)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712037720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-01%2Fs400-missile-reuters_650x400_51515843330.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-growing-defence-needs-can-soon-force-it-to-make-a-tough-choice-5356946%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20needs%20more%20sophisticated%20technology%20than%20what%20Russia%20can%20offer%20today.%20There%20is%20now%20a%20complex%20choice%20that%20it%20has%20avoided%20making%20for%20years%3A%20rely%20on%20Western%20states%20led%20by%20the%20US%20or%20on%20an%20increasingly%20inconsistent%20Russia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-growing-defence-needs-can-soon-force-it-to-make-a-tough-choice-5356946%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-growing-defence-needs-can-soon-force-it-to-make-a-tough-choice-5356946%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-growing-defence-n