f%20the%20projects%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20during%20his%20service%20because%20they%20were%20confidential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20if%20he%20did%20get%20called%20up%20for%20an%20interview%2C%20Tan%20said%20he%20had%20to%20battle%20the%20negative%20stereotypes%20recruiters%20might%20have%20toward%20former%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mental%20model%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20for%20military%20personnel%20is%20that%20they%20are%20very%20rigid%2C%20they%20do%20not%20have%20any%20relevant%20skill%20sets%20or%20experiences%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20was%20fortunate%20that%20Euromonitor%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20chance%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYap%20faced%20a%20similar%20experience.%20Before%20he%20landed%20his%20first%20corporate%20job%2C%20Yap%20said%20he%20sent%20out%20many%20resumes%20and%20talked%20to%20many%20different%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20former%20commando%20told%20BI%20that%20veterans%20could%20still%20rely%20on%20their%20military%20experience%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%20What's%20more%20important%2C%20Yap%20said%2C%20is%20knowing%20how%20to%20apply%20those%20experiences%20based%20on%20the%20business's%20goals%20and%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20take%20principles%20from%20military%20life%20and%20apply%20them%20in%20a%20different%20context%2C%20like%20business%20operations%2C%20naturally%2C%20not%20all%20of%20them%20will%20be%20relevant%2C%26quot%3B%20Yap%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20times%20when%20you'll%20go%20with%20your%20gut%20and%20times%20when%20you%20need%20to%20think%20objectively%20about%20things.%20You%20just%20have%20to%20be%20very%20honest%20with%20yourself%20about%20what's%20working%20or%20not%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaking%20it%20as%20a%20veteran%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20is%20all%20about%20playing%20to%20your%20strengths%2C%20using%20your%20network%2C%20and%20being%20resilient%